BP Plc and  Royal Dutch Shell Plc (RDSA) 
are separately considering a partnership with  Eni SpA (ENI)  in
Mozambiqiue, the  Independent on Sunday  reported, without saying
where it got the information.  Eni is seeking to sell part of its 70 percent stake in the
Area-4 field in the east African nation, according to the
newspaper. The companies may be mulling a 20 percent stake,
which would be valued at $4 billion, the Independent said.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
